You can't deal that level of damage without the backup.  Thus, dispite the fact that the 4! support classes in the group do FAR less damage than the wizards, it makes sense to group with them.<br>
<br>
The PBAOE group's problem is that not enough classes are useful in them, and the group size of 6 is just barely enough for them to start scaling.  Add useful PBAOE spells/abilities to all the classes(3), and up XP group sizes to 12 (XP-join 2 groups), and actually DESIGN some zones around this interesting tactic.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, this is getting too specific.<br>
<br>
Losing snare probably isn't going to happen -- the cries of nerf would echo thru the lands.  Thus, wizard DD beating rogue DPH won't happen.  Other spells have to be used to make wizard attractive to grouping.<br>
<br>
Al'kabors looks like the most tempting victem to modify for a wizard's groupage.  Either that, or rain spells.(4)<br>
<br>
What if rain spells hit:<br>
1 target first wave<br>
2 targets 2nd wave<br>
3 targets 3rd wave<br>
<br>
It would up their efficiency 50% on 3 targets, and 25% on 2.<br>
<br>
&quot;Focus Items&quot; for particular rains spells could be added, giving an extra wave for that spell (with a number of target determined by the item).<br>
<br>
Or, like I've said before, double Al'kabor damage to stationary targets, and make it bounce off mezzed mobs.<br>
<br>
Or, add in near-melee-range DDs for wizards.<br>
<br>
