<br>
You have reduced entire game balancing down to damage in an xp situation.  Whether it is grouping, soloing, or raiding, xp is not the only goal, niether is damage per hour.  If your goal is killing Master Yael in the Hole, you need damage per hour until you reach the master, then you need damage per second as you kill him.<br>
<br>
Your goal need not be considered a &quot;raid.&quot;  For example, I spent several hours tonight alone in Kedge Keep soloing.  I was soloing, yes, but not for xp and not for loot.  I was trying to kill several mobs that were there just for the fun of figuring it out.  I got about 5% alt xp for my efforts, and ended up taking a 75% rez after a death.  Overall though,  it was one of the more fun nights I have had in EQ.  (I've never been big on high risk soloing before)<br>
<br>
My goal was not damage per hour.  My goal was exploration and the assassination of a couple mobs (Undertow,  Swirlspine Searhorse, to be precise).  Tools of varying importance to me during this time:<br>
<br>
Improved Invis<br>
EB item<br>
Annul Magic for thorn shields<br>
Pet dps<br>
Fast Nuke dps.<br>
Pet Heal per second<br>
Pet heal per mana<br>
<br>
I would be hard pressed to say which was most important, but since I was so relaxed and cautious spent much more time meditating than I needed.<br>
<br>
This was a solo situation, but it need not have been.<br>
<br>
I have hunted many places with friends, for reasons other than socialization.  We usually group to play the game, not grind max xp per hour.  I do not believe this is mere socialization.<br>
<br>
Why is this important?<br>
<br>
Because the value of a wizard increases in these situations.<br>
<br>
These are the two situations that must be balanced with each other.  In the XP grind situation, mana is a big limitation.  In the raid/mini-raid/adventure setting, mana/DPH is sometimes a limitation, sometimes only a minor limitation, and sometimes not a limitation at all.  In adventure settings, wizards already have great potential.  In many situations their dps is practically limited only by aggro and their ability to cast spells.<br>
<br>
While not everyone is content to have fun and explore, not everyone wants to be tuned only for max xp gain, especially if tuning them for balanced max group xp gain makes them overly powerful outside of that one environment.<br>
